<br>
As you all know, the JP Gnoll Invasion Event is triggered by the killing of Barducks Darkpaw, who spawns on a 24 hour timer.  We have a good record of killing Mr. Darkpaw, but not of completing the invasion event.<br>
<br>
The event has four waves of increasingly stronger gnolls.  Each wave attacks the three buildings in JP.  The gnolls attempt to kill the NPCs in the buildings.  The event happens about three to five minutes after Barducks dies.<br>
<br>
After the four waves are defeated, a megaboss gnoll spawns and attacks.  This megaboss has not been spawned by any guild since the event was on test server.  Most guilds feel the loot potential of this quest isn't high enough to try and finish the quest.<br>
<br>
As the event proceeds, the gnolls drop items that you turn in to get rewards.  The quality of the rewards are based on the difficulty of the gnoll that dropped it (which wave he was from) and the # of NPCs that survive the event.  To get the true rewards of this quest no NPCs can die and all the gnoll waves must be defeated, including the boss gnoll.<br>
<br>
I don't think we can defeat this event alone, but a large enough raid force (30+) of 50+ levels probably could.  At least 6 people need to be camped at each house when the event starts.  They can defeat the first wave while the killers of Darkpaw return.  12 people should kill Darkpaw and 18 more at the town at least.  After that, the 30 can stop the remainder of waves, with the 12 people splitting into groups of 4 and joining the other groups (so 10 are at each house).<br>
<br>
I'm not sure this is something we want to do, but it might be something fun to do at some point in the future, if we feel like it. <p>--<br>
